content:
Create and Assign a Broadcaster Permission Set for SMS

Available in: Lightning Experience. View required editions 
This article applies to: Standard SMS channels 

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To create permission sets: Manage Profiles and Permission Sets
To assign permission sets: Assign Permission Sets

Create a permission set for broadcasters.
From Setup, enter Permission Sets, and then select Permission Sets.
Click New.
For Label, enter a name for the permission set. The API Name is automatically filled.
Save your changes.

In Object Settings | Messaging Sessions, give view access to all and edit permissions for users or roles. Click Save.
In Object Settings | Messaging Users, give view access to all and edit permissions for users or roles. Click Save.

Go back to Permission Set Overview page and select App Permissions. Enable Agent Initiated Outbound Messaging, Messaging Agent, and Send One-to-Many Messages. Click Save.

Assign the permission set you created.
From Setup, enter Users, and select Users.
Select the name of the user that you want to assign the permission set to.
Under Permission Set Assignments, click Edit Assignments.
Move the permission set that you created to the Enabled Permission Sets list.
Save your changes.
title: Creating a Broadcaster Permission Set for SMS
